Annie: Hey Betty, look. It seems like rabbit brain here can trip herself too.
Betty: Perhaps those big dumb ears of hers are messing with her balance?
Annie: What are you staring at?
Betty: A worthless scum from the Slums wants to study with us? Get lost.
Cara: Ouch!
Leah: My, my. Are you alright my dear seniors? Apologies; the eggs just flew out when I tripped myself back there.
Cara: So the eggs really do fly out after a really long delay?
Betty: Idiot! Have some common sense! She's definitely messing with us!
Annie: UGH! You little... I'll teach you a lesson!
Leah: Haha~ take care, my dear seniors. Look where you walk though; you don't wanna trip~
Charle: What's it that you find so amusing?
Leah: Well, you see, I...
Leah: ... Headmaster Ceres~Those three were bullying me...

Charle: Ladies, are you injured? 
Please go to the infirmary and rest for now.
Charle: Miss Leah, please come with me.
Leah: Okay......
Charle: Miss Leah, can you tell me what just happened back there?
Leah: Headmaster~ it's all their fault.  It has absolutely nothing to do with me.
Charle: In Rune Academy, the misuse of Rune magic in personal issues can lead to severe punishment, including expulsion. Do you realize that?
Leah: They tripped me first, that's why I pulled a prank on them using Rune magic. Also, it was three of them against me; that's why I...
Charle: So does that mean you can attack your seniors with Rune magic?
Leah: N-No, it doesn't.
Charle: Alright, a decision has been made. This will be Miss Leah's punishment!
Leah: What?
Charle: As long as Miss Leah brings me the Tana Root from Whistlewood Valley before sunrise tomorrow,
Charle: I will pretend that nothing ever happened. If you can't, I'll have no choice but to expel you.
Leah: Expelled!?
